# <type>(<scope>): <summary>
#
# Match the existing repository style:
#   feat: add lark agent core conversation slice
#   test: enable pytest async tests
#   docs: add project readme
#   chore(task): archive lark-agent-bot-core
#   chore: record lark agent core session
#   init: init repo
#
# Subject:
#   <type>(<optional-scope>): <imperative summary>
#   Keep it concise and lowercase after the type when natural.
#
# Common types:
#   feat      user-visible feature or capability
#   fix       bug fix
#   test      test-only change
#   docs      documentation-only change
#   refactor  internal restructure without behavior change
#   chore     repository, tooling, generated, or Trellis workflow change
#   init      repository initialization
#
# Trellis finish-work sequence:
#   1. Work commit:      <type>(<scope>): <summary>
#   2. Archive commit:   chore(task): archive <task-name>
#   3. Journal commit:   chore: record <session summary>
#
# Optional body, when the subject is not enough:
#   Why:
#   - ...
#
#   What:
#   - ...
#
#   Validation:
#   - ...
